
---


@startuml
' Entities and classes for LabTracker system

class Doctor {
    - name: String
    - address: String
    - phoneNumber: String
    - practitionerNumber: String
    - signatureImage: Image
}

class Patient {
    - healthNumber: String
    - name: String
    - dateOfBirth: Date
    - address: String
    - phoneNumber: String
}

class Requisition {
    - validityDate: Date
    - tests: List<Test>
    - repetitionCount: Integer
    - repetitionInterval: IntervalEnum
    - doctor: Doctor
    - patient: Patient
}

enum IntervalEnum {
    Weekly
    Monthly
    HalfYearly
    Yearly
}

class Test {
    - testName: String
    - testGroup: TestGroup
    - duration: Duration
    - isAppointmentRequired: Boolean
    - isSampleBased: Boolean
    - requisition: Requisition
}

enum TestGroup {
    BloodTest
    Ultrasound
    XRay
    UrineTest
    StoolTest
}

class Lab {
    - labName: String
    - address: String
    - registrationNumber: String
    - businessHours: BusinessHours
    - cancellationFee: Double
}

class BusinessHours {
    - startTime: Time
    - endTime: Time
}

class Appointment {
    - confirmationNumber: String
    - appointmentDate: Date
    - startTime: Time
    - endTime: Time
    - lab: Lab
    - test: Test
    - patient: Patient
}

class Result {
    - resultType: ResultType
    - report: String
    - test: Test
}

enum ResultType {
    Positive
    Negative
}

' Relationships

Doctor "1" -- "0..*" Requisition : creates
Requisition "1" -- "1" Doctor : belongsTo
Requisition "1" -- "1" Patient : belongsTo
Patient "1" -- "0..*" Requisition : has
Requisition "1" -- "1..*" Test : includes
Test "1" -- "1" TestGroup : belongsTo
Test "1" -- "0..1" Appointment : scheduledAt
Test "1" -- "1" Result : has
Lab "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : offers
Lab "1" -- "1" BusinessHours : has
Appointment "1" -- "1" Lab : at
Patient "1" -- "0..*" Appointment : makes

@enduml

---

### 📝 Notes:

- **Doctor** can create multiple **Requisitions** for **Patients**, but not for themselves.
- A **Requisition** contains one or more **Tests** from the same **TestGroup**.
- Each **Test** may require an **Appointment** depending on the type.
- **Labs** have fixed **BusinessHours** and can be selected by **Patients** for appointments.
- **Results** are linked back to a specific **Test**.
- The **IntervalEnum** supports weekly, monthly, half-yearly, and yearly repetition patterns.
- **TestGroup** ensures that only compatible tests can be grouped together in a requisition.

